     -------------------------------------------------------------
     Title.................: Blot Virus
     Aliases...............: FAT, Screen, Swiss
     Detected When.........: May 1988
              Where........: Amherst (USA)
     Type Of Virus.........: Bootsector
     Length Of Virus.......: 681 bytes (Bootsector + 1 FAT sector)
     ------------------------Pre-Conditions-----------------------
     Operating System(s)...: Atari TOS
     Version/Release.......: TOS 1.2 upwards
     Computer Model(s).....: All models
     ------------------------Attributes---------------------------
     Infection Trigger.....: Accessing new disk in drive A
     Media Affected........: Drive A
     Interrupts Hooked.....: Horizontal Blank Interrupt
                             Hdv_bpb vector
                             Critical error handler
                             Phystop is decremented by 1K
     Damage................: Screen is blacked out from bottom to
                             middle & from top to middle at the
                             same time
     Damage Trigger........: Approx 3 hours after virus infection
     Particularities.......: Only non-executable bootsector are
                             infected
     Similaraties..........: ----


     -------------------------------------------------------------
     Title.................: C'T Virus
     Aliases...............: ----
     Detected When.........: ----
              Where........: ----
     Type Of Virus.........: Bootsector, Reset-resident
     Length Of Virus.......: 512 bytes
     ------------------------Pre-Conditions-----------------------
     Operating System(s)...: Atari TOS
     Version/Release.......: All versions
     Computer Model(s).....: All models
     ------------------------Attributes---------------------------
     Infection Trigger.....: Each time a disk is changed
     Media Affected........: Drives A & B (Damages hard disks)
     Interrupts Hooked.....: Hdv_bpb & Hdv_mediach vectors
     Damage................: Damage can only occur when a hard
                             disk is conected. Because of an
                             error in the virus, the partition
                             information will be destroyed, when
                             the virus tries to infect the hard
                             disk.
                             The following message is displayed
                             after every 20 infections:
                             "ARRRGGGHHH Diskvirus hat wiedr
                             zugeschlagen"
     Damage Trigger........: After infection counter reaches 20
     Particularities.......: Has a major bug that makes it easy
                             to spot. If a disk is write protected
                             and the virus tries to infect it, the
                             write protect error message is
                             displayed (even when you're reading
                             the disk!!!)
     Similaraties..........: ----
     Special Comment.......: This virus was featured as a type in
                             listing in a German computer magazine
                             , with information on how to modify
                             it. Therefore there may be many
                             versions.


